#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:1
msgid "Release Process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:3
msgid ""
"This document provides a high-level overview of the VTK release cycle and "
"associated release process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:6
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:8
msgid ""
"We aim to release a new version of VTK every six months. However, we "
"recognize that this schedule is flexible. The project is funded and "
"developed by many different groups, each of which works towards their own "
"particular sets of features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:13
msgid "VTK releases are named with a `Major.Minor.Patch` scheme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:15
msgid ""
"VTK releases are handled by the VTK release group, which currently consists "
"of:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:16
msgid "@vbolea"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:17
msgid "@sankhesh"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:18
msgid "@mwestphal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:20
msgid "Branching Scheme"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:22
msgid ""
"The overall release history resembles a skinny tree. Development proceeds "
"along the `master` branch, consisting of topic branches that start from and "
"are merged into `master`. Every so often, a release is tagged and branched "
"from it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:26
msgid ""
"In general, no work takes place on the `release` branch, but some bug fixes "
"from master can be backported and will be used for occasional patch releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:30
msgid ""
"Steps for contributing changes specific to the `release` branch are "
"documented in [](git/develop.md#create-a-topic)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:34
msgid ""
"On the `master` branch, bug fixes and new features are continuously "
"developed. At release time, the focus temporarily shifts to producing a "
"library that is as stable and robust as possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:38
msgid "Steps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:40
msgid "The process for cutting releases is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:42
msgid "Announce upcoming release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:44
msgid ""
"A few weeks before the intended `release` branch, the VTK release group "
"announce on [VTK Discourse](https://discourse.vtk.org/) that a new release "
"is coming. This alerts developers to avoid making drastic changes that might "
"delay the release and gives them a chance to push important and nearly "
"completed features in time for the release. For example, see [this post]"
"(https://discourse.vtk.org/t/vtk-9-4-0-release/14577)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:50
msgid ""
"Polish the dashboards and bug tracker by addressing outstanding issue and "
"coordinate effort with relevant developers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:53
msgid ""
"Persistent compilation and regression test problems are fixed. Serious "
"outstanding bugs are fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:56
msgid "This is an effort involving the whole community of developers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:58
msgid ""
"[Create a new issue](https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/issues/new) titled "
"`Release X.Y.Z[rcN]` based of the [new-release](https://gitlab.kitware.com/"
"vtk/vtk/-/blob/master/.gitlab/issue_templates/new-release.md?plain=1) "
"template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:62
msgid ""
"Specific steps to create eiter the candidate or the official release are "
"found in the newly created issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:66
msgid "This is handled by the VTK release group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:68
msgid "Perform the release candidate cycle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:70
msgid ""
"Tag the release branch and create and publish release candidate artifacts "
"and change summaries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:73
msgid ""
"Announce the release candidate and request feedback from the community, "
"especially third-party packagers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:77
msgid ""
"Bug reports should be entered into the bug tracker with the upcoming release "
"number as the milestone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:81
msgid ""
"If the community reports bugs, classify them in the bug tracker and ensure "
"they are fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:84
msgid ""
"This is not handled by the VTK release group but by the whole community of "
"VTK developers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:87
msgid ""
"Only serious bugs and regressions need to be fixed before the release. Such "
"merge requests must be acknowledged (`+1`) by the VTK release group before "
"being merged. New features and minor problems should be merged into `master` "
"as usual."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:92
msgid ""
"Patches for the release branch should start from the release branch, be "
"submitted through GitLab, and then merged into `master`. Once fully tested "
"there, reviewed and acknowloedge by the VTK release group, the branch can be "
"merged into the release branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:97
msgid ""
"When the selected issues are fixed in the release branch, tag the tip of the "
"release branch and release it as the next candidate, then the cycle "
"continues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:101
msgid ""
"Distribution specific patches can accumulate over time. Consider reviewing "
"the following distribution specific pages to identify potential fixes and "
"improvements that could be integrated in VTK itself:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:105
msgid "Debian:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:106
msgid "https://tracker.debian.org/pkg/vtk9"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:107
msgid "https://udd.debian.org/patches.cgi?src=vtk9"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:109
msgid "Gentoo:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:110
msgid "https://packages.gentoo.org/packages/sci-libs/vtk"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:111
msgid "https://gitweb.gentoo.org/repo/gentoo.git/tree/sci-libs/vtk/files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:113
msgid "openSUSE:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:114
msgid "https://build.opensuse.org/package/show/openSUSE:Factory/vtk"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:116
msgid "Package the official release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:118
msgid ""
"The official VTK package consists of tar balls and ZIP files of the source, "
"Python Wheels, Doxygen documentation, and regression test data, all at the "
"tag point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:122
msgid ""
"Volunteer third-party packagers create binary packages from the official "
"release for various platforms, so their input is especially valuable during "
"the release cycle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:126
msgid ""
"The VTK release group also compiles release notes for the official release "
"announcement. Release notes are compiled from various [standardized topic "
"documents](https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/tree/master/Documentation/"
"release) added to the `Documentation/release/dev` folder while features or "
"issues are fixed. The aggregation of these topic files is done manually and "
"results in the creation of a file named `Documentation/release/X.Y.md` for "
"the current release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:133
msgid "GitLab and Releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:135
msgid ""
"GitLab milestones are used for keeping track of branches for the release. "
"They allow keeping track of issues and merge requests which should be "
"\"done\" for the milestone to be considered complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:139
msgid ""
"For each release (including release candidates), a milestone is created with "
"a plausible due date. The milestone page allows for an easy overview of "
"branches which need wrangling for a release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:143
msgid "Merge Requests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:145
msgid ""
"Merge requests which need to be rebased onto the relevant release branch "
"should be marked with the `needs-rebase-for-release` tag and commented on "
"how the branch can be rebased properly:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:149
msgid ""
"This branch is marked for a release, but includes other commits in\n"
"`master`. Please either rebase the branch on top of the release branch and\n"
"remove the `needs-rebase-for-release` tag from the merge request:\n"
"\n"
"```sh\n"
"$ git rebase --onto=origin/release origin/master $branch_name\n"
"$ git gitlab-push -f\n"
"```\n"
"\n"
"or, if there are conflicts when using a single branch, open a new branch\n"
"and open a merge request against the `release` branch:\n"
"\n"
"```sh\n"
"$ git checkout -b ${branch_name}-release $branch_name\n"
"$ git rebase --onto=origin/release origin/master ${branch_name}-release\n"
"$ git gitlab-push\n"
"```\n"
"\n"
"Thanks!\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:169
msgid "Wrangling Branches"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:171
msgid ""
"Branches may be wrangled using the filters in the merge request page. "
"Replace `$release` at the end with the relevant milestone name:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:174
msgid ""
"https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/merge_requests?"
"state=all&milestone_title=$release\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:176
msgid ""
"The following states of a merge request indicate where they are in the flow:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:178
msgid "open for `master`: get into `master` first"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:179
msgid "open for `release`: ensure it is already in `master`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:180
msgid ""
"open with `needs-rebase-for-release` tag: wait for contributor to rebase "
"properly; ping if necessary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:182
msgid "`MERGED`: merge into `release`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/release_process.md:184
msgid ""
"There is currently no good way of marking a branch that went towards "
"`master` is also in `release` already since tags cannot be added to closed "
"merge requests. Suggestions welcome :) ."
msgstr ""
